Here are some things for working with Perl in Emacs.  Click the title heading to search for more pages about [::Perl].

== Development environments ==

* PerlDevelopEnvironment is a bundle of perl-related elisp distributed as a CPAN package called [http://search.cpan.org/dist/Emacs-PDE Emacs::PDE].

* [[Sepia]] is an Elisp package for interactive Perl development, available as a CPAN package called [http://search.cpan.org/dist/Sepia/ Sepia]. 

* [http://search.cpan.org/dist/Devel-PerlySense/ PerlySense] is a  Perl IDE back-end that integrates with editor front-ends,
currently Emacs.

* [https://github.com/aki2o/emacs-plsense emacs-plsense] is an extension to Emacs that provides interface to [https://github.com/aki2o/plsense PlSense].

== Support packages ==

* PerlNow: perlnow.el is an emacs package that fills in some gaps in emacs perl support.
It makes heavy use of the template.el package (TemplatesMode).

** PerlTemplates -- alternate approach using the emacs-standard skeleton.el for templating

* [http://www.gentei.org/~yuuji/software/ perlplus.el] -- editing completion for local and global variables and functions

* PerlPodCoding -- coding system from <code>=encoding</code> line

* PerlPodGt -- helpers for <code>C<...></code> POD markup

* PerlPodPreview -- preview formatted POD

* [http://user42.tuxfamily.org/compilation-perl/index.html compilation-perl.el] -- <code>compilation-mode</code> error regexps for <code>podchecker</code>, <code>Test</code> and <code>xsubpp</code>

* [http://user42.tuxfamily.org/perl-quote/index.html perl-quote.el] -- switch strings between double or single quotes

* [http://user42.tuxfamily.org/perl-use-utf8-coding/index.html perl-use-utf8-coding.el] -- coding system from ##use utf8## pragma

* [http://user42.tuxfamily.org/pst-format/index.html pst-format.el] -- decode "Storable" module files for human reading

* Lisp:xs-mode.el -- using CcMode and some font lock on <code>.xs</code> files

* [http://user42.tuxfamily.org/ffap-perl-module/index.html ffap-perl-module.el] -- extend <code>M-x ffap</code> to go to perl module source files

* [http://user42.tuxfamily.org/man-completion/index.html man-completion.el] -- notice perl module name at point for <code>M-x man</code>

* PerlCompletion -- A pure-elisp completion package.

* [http://github.com/jrockway/stylish/tree/master Stylish] -- An interactive mode.

* [http://web-mode.org web-mode.el] -- Major mode for editing template-toolkit (tt) templates.

* [https://github.com/vividsnow/perl-live perl-live] -- perl live coding

== Related modes ==

* [http://www.shellarchive.co.uk/content/emacs.html] -- A perl compilation mode with syntax highlighting and the usual compilation stuff.

* PodMode -- simple editing of <code>.pod</code> files or POD within code

* YamlMode -- for editing <code>META.yml</code> files (if you do that directly)

== Other topics ==

* CPerlMode is preferable to PerlMode.  It has some set-up oddities, which are dicussed on the CPerlMode page.

* IndentingPerl -- The only other option is TurnAllIndentingOff.

* PerlTidyElisp -- An interactive function that calls perltidy on a buffer or region.

* Some attempts have been made at tight integration of perl and emacs: 
** PerlMacs -- embedding a perl interpreter (essentially deprecated)
** EmacsEpl -- interprocess communication

* DateCalc -- date calculations using the perl/C modules Date::Calc and Date::Manip.

* The PerlAdvocacy page exists for discussing perl's merits.

==External Links==

; A discussion of using emacs as a perl IDE:
http://obsidianrook.com/perlnow/emacs_as_perl_ide.html

; A quick start guide (a "rosetta") for perl programmers interested in elisp:
http://obsidianrook.com/devnotes/elisp-for-perl-programmers.html

